March 3 at 4:25 PM ¬∑

We are so proud of Global Preparatory Academy Indy at Riverside #44's student choir who performed at last week's
USPS 43rd Black Heritage Ceremony to unveil a stamp honoring Gwen Ifill. Congratulations on an incredible performance! Indianapolis Public Schools Indiana Historical Society

"Our goal is to prepare our children, and putting these kids in front of different types of audiences and audience sizes exposes them to opportunities, but it also prepares them for life outside of class." -- Founder and School Leader Mariama Shaheed

Dear Families,

Due to driver call offs, IPS is unable to run our regular school bus routes in a safe and efficient manner today.

Schools will remain open however, students not able to attend school will not be marked absent.

Meal service will be provided. Teachers and staff will be present to receive students.

We apologize for this inconvenience.
